$ System.Threading.Tasks.Task (class)

A `System.Threading.Tasks.Task` object represents an asynchronous operation.

Such `Task` objects are central to the *Task-Based Asynchronous Pattern (TAP)*.

The `Main()` entry point can, starting with → development/languages/C-Sharp[C#] 7.1, return a `Task` or a `Task<int>`.

sa:
  There is also a «templatized» version of this class: → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Threading/Tasks/Task-TResult[`System.Threading.Tasks.Task<TResult>`] which in fact derives from
`Task`.
